<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/81470286-alexander-alexander">Alexander Alexander</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I think its not about the age, but how interesetd you are in Technology and physics. Reynolds IS a scientist, who worked for ESA, which deeply affects<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I think its not about the age, but how interesetd you are in Technology and physics. Reynolds IS a scientist, who worked for ESA, which deeply affects his books. <br />I read it when i was 15 i understood most of it. But sometimes (especialy, when he talks about quantumphysics) it was too hard. Now (after 2 years of Computer Science and Math studies) i think a understand everything he is talking about :D<br />Dont get me wrong: i love this book! <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
