<div id="review_4148299" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4148299" />
    <a title="Adam" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/214053-adam"><img alt="Adam" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1216438982p2/214053.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4148299?book_show_action=true">Aug 06, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Adam" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Adam" href="/user/show/214053-adam">Adam</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">fans of intelligent horror and scifi</span></div>

        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4148299" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13005673569092221187">If your fan of the wing of scifi represented in the mainstream by movies like Ridley Scott&apos;s Alien and John Carpenter&apos;s The Thing(or more recently Danny Boyles&apos;Sunshine)than this book will be endless entertainment for for you. Barely human nightmare show characters you wouldn&apos;t want to be in a dark alley with, discovering a universe filled with lovecraftian horror. Similiar to Delany&apos;s Nova and Swanwick&apos;s Vacuum Flowers with identity confusion straight out of Gene Wolfe land plus aliens as weird</span>
  <span id="freeText13005673569092221187" style="display:none">If your fan of the wing of scifi represented in the mainstream by movies like Ridley Scott's Alien and John Carpenter's The Thing(or more recently Danny Boyles'Sunshine)than this book will be endless entertainment for for you. Barely human nightmare show characters you wouldn't want to be in a dark alley with, discovering a universe filled with lovecraftian horror. Similiar to Delany's Nova and Swanwick's Vacuum Flowers with identity confusion straight out of Gene Wolfe land plus aliens as weird as Lem's or Lovecraft's. Mind bending tech meets horror and non stop tension and a rising feeling of of dread mixing a sense of absolute wonder. A space ship designed Edgar Allen Poe, barren moons, Boschian cities, huge alien machines, all add to the grim, doomy atmosphere making this thrilling gothic sci fi. Along with Meiville,Reynolds is a new author bring some new vibrant life into genre fiction. </span>
  <a data-text-id="13005673569092221187" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


